## What does Word Predictor App do?

  • Word Predictor App will try to predict next word based on last three words the sentence. This app also provides five most likely words using corpus data from from Capstone Dataset. The files in the data set are en_US_twitter.txt,en_US_news.txt and en_US_blogs.txt.

How does it work?

  • From given corpus data, a sample (20% of original dataset) was selected for building the prediction engine. [see sampleData.r] (https://github.com/dxrodri/datasciencecoursera/tree/master/SwiftKeyCapstone). Using this sample data, a prediction algorithm was build using R tm package. A lookup datagrams for bigrams, trigrams and quadgrams was build using the TermDocumentMatrix function.

How does it work (continued)?

Frequency distribution for each grams was calculated and smoothing techniques using Simple Good Turing algorithm was then applied for each grams. Given a sentence, the prediction algorithms selects five probable words given the weightage for matched grams as follows: 50% for quadrams,30% to trigrams and 20% for bigrams. [see predictFunctions_V1.r] (https://github.com/dxrodri/datasciencecoursera/tree/master/SwiftKeyCapstone).
